# Sass Installation - ALX Intermediate Frontend

## Objective:
Set up Sass in a local development environment for styling with SCSS.

## Project Directory:
`0x03-sass_scss`

---

## Step-by-Step Installation

### 1. Create Project Directory
```bash
mkdir 0x03-sass_scss
cd 0x03-sass_scss

### 2. Install Node Version Manager (NVM)
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

### 3. Reload Terminal or Run the Following
export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"
[ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"
[ -s "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion"

### 4. Install Node.js (e.g. version 20.16)
nvm install 20.16.0
nvm use 20.16.0

### 5. Install Sass Using npm
npm install sass -v 3.7.4

### 6. Installed Sass via npm
npm install -g sass
